<br>
Here's an example... let's say that in issue 2 of Washboard Abs Man, our hero is suffering from guilt because he's caused the death of a bad guy rather than just giving him prison for life. You might do something like his arms curving around against his will to point a knife in his own face. This shows more symbolically the theme of the book.<br>
<br>
Example 2: In issue 5 of Washboard Abs Man, our hero starts to realize that he could be earning truckloads of money to do his heroic deeds, but he's been doing it for free, and he's having a moral conflict over the issue. A less exciting approach would be drawing people trying to give him money. A more symbolic way to do it would be to draw a coin with Washboard Abs Man seemingly trapped inside of it.<br>
<br>
See what I mean? People get to see the literal actions in the book, give 'em something more symbolic for the cover! :P<br>
